                            <comment id="110312" author="jrduncans" created="Wed, 3 Dec 2014 17:05:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I don&apos;t think just a documentation fix would be sufficient.  This basically makes it impossible to set the cache-control security settings while also allowing caching for desired resources.  I agree that it seems hard in the current architecture; I think the minimum that could be done is to allow configuration of Spring-Security headers on a URL instead of just globally, like:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; http&lt;br/&gt;
      // ...&lt;br/&gt;
      .antMatchers(&quot;/resources/**&quot;)&lt;br/&gt;
          .headers().contentTypeOptions().frameOptions().httpStrictTransportSecurity().xssProtection();&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Obviously, it would also be nice to have a syntax for just disabling the cache control instead of having to specify everything but that header set, but that&apos;s just a nice-to-have.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
